            <thetext>hello,

i think i found a bug in qx.ui.layout.Grid().

adding widgets to a grid does not produce a runtime error when using colSpans.

for example:

form.add(widget1,{row:5,column:3});
form.add(widget2,{row:5,column:3});

will produce a widget-add-error.

but:

form.add(widget1,{row:5,column:2});
form.add(widget2,{row:5,column:0,colSpan:3});

will not produce any error.

but when tabing / shift-tabing over the widgets will blend in the overlayed widget in the upper-left corner without any editing/focusing posiblity.

greeting
julian</thetext>
